						<text>
							Opossums have a prehensile tail, which they use to grasp a tree safely while climbing.  They have dextrous paws and opposable big toes, which allow them to walk along tree branches and handle food items.  Opossums are marsupials and moms carry their babies around in pouches. Later, the babies will ride on mom&#8217;s back while she looks for food.
						</text>
